01:06:09.598 --> 01:06:12.692
- with some sort of nice kind of direction.
- Yeah, yeah. You've got it too.

01:06:12.835 --> 01:06:15.395
- What are you talking about?
- Yeah, those rough edges.

01:06:15.538 --> 01:06:17.472
I mean, don't get me wrong,
it's beautiful.

01:06:18.040 --> 01:06:20.975
Thanks. Hey, what's not beautiful to you?
You know?

01:06:21.110 --> 01:06:25.774
See? You did it again.
That's it, you got that focus.

01:06:25.915 --> 01:06:29.908
But that's how we're alike, Wally,
we're both determined.

01:06:30.052 --> 01:06:34.079
Sebastian may be, uh,
resistant to me now, but I'll get through.

01:06:34.223 --> 01:06:37.283
Life throws you curveballs,
that's for sure, right?

01:06:37.426 --> 01:06:39.758
I mean, a few months ago,
I was planning on having children

01:06:39.895 --> 01:06:42.125
with a woman
who I'm pretty sure I'll never see again.

01:06:43.265 --> 01:06:44.732
A few months ago?

01:06:44.867 --> 01:06:46.266
- Yep.
- That's it, huh?

01:06:46.402 --> 01:06:49.838
And now I'm crazy about a woman
who paid me for my sperm.

01:06:50.940 --> 01:06:52.601
How about that curveball?

01:06:53.042 --> 01:06:54.475
Bam!

01:06:55.144 --> 01:06:58.671
Sebastian's gonna get through this.
We're gonna lick this thing.

01:06:58.814 --> 01:07:03.012
He doesn't need to have this dark cloud
hanging over his head.

01:07:03.152 --> 01:07:04.779
What do you think,
you want another beer?

01:07:04.920 --> 01:07:07.013
WALLY: Oh, the guy was just...
He just would not stop.

01:07:07.156 --> 01:07:08.851
He just kept going
and talking and talking.

01:07:08.991 --> 01:07:12.119
You know, he thinks that it's his kid.
He thinks that he's my best friend.

01:07:12.261 --> 01:07:15.697
Wants me to give him advice on how
to be a better father to my son, you know?

01:07:15.831 --> 01:07:17.628
It's just like a nightmare.
He's e-mailing me.

01:07:17.766 --> 01:07:20.496
He's smiling at me all the time.
He's hitting me with the big teeth.

01:07:20.636 --> 01:07:22.900
- Wants me to go fly-fishing with him.
- Yeah, and why...?

01:07:23.038 --> 01:07:24.505
I don't understand. Why are we here?

01:07:24.640 --> 01:07:27.609
Because I gotta exchange this frame.
Sebastian wants one from the new line.

01:07:27.743 --> 01:07:30.871
- It's a sterling-silver 5-by-7.
- Oh, I see.

01:07:31.013 --> 01:07:33.675
Well, that's so nice that
you're taking an interest in his hobbies,

01:07:33.816 --> 01:07:36.614
but, um, listen,
I think the first order of business

01:07:36.752 --> 01:07:38.720
is for you to take care of this thing
with Kassie.

01:07:38.854 --> 01:07:40.515
Why are we waiting? Why the wait?

01:07:40.656 --> 01:07:43.022
Please, I know that, all right?
I've been trying to do that.

01:07:43.158 --> 01:07:45.854
- But everything is all turned around now.
- Turned around?

01:07:46.662 --> 01:07:49.358
I'm turned around.

01:07:49.498 --> 01:07:52.695
That night,
she said she thought we had energy.

01:07:52.835 --> 01:07:55.895
Ooh. That's a new twist.
Never heard that before.

01:07:56.038 --> 01:07:57.096
It was very weird though.

01:07:57.239 --> 01:07:59.264
Her mouth is saying
she's spending time with Roland,

01:07:59.408 --> 01:08:01.137
but her eyes are screaming, "Save me!"

01:08:01.277 --> 01:08:03.905
Ah. So go with that. Go with the eyes.

01:08:04.046 --> 01:08:07.914
And now I think
that I have feelings for her.

01:08:08.951 --> 01:08:12.648
Really? You think so?
It's only been, uh, 13 years.

01:08:13.122 --> 01:08:15.488
Please, I know you've been saying that
for a very long time.

01:08:15.624 --> 01:08:18.092
- Now I'm finally saying it.
- Well, this is all good news.

01:08:18.227 --> 01:08:20.559
That's just... You're in love
with the mother of your child.

01:08:20.696 --> 01:08:22.186
Meanwhile, she's falling for Roland.

01:08:22.331 --> 01:08:25.164
And I know that I could save all of this
by just telling her the truth,

01:08:25.301 --> 01:08:28.168
but if I do that, I lose everything, right?

01:08:29.571 --> 01:08:31.471
And if you don't?

01:08:31.974 --> 01:08:35.102
Then I'll never be more
than Uncle Wally.

01:08:36.312 --> 01:08:37.438
That's no good.

01:08:37.579 --> 01:08:39.342
WALLY: Hi, excuse me.
- Yes?

01:08:39.481 --> 01:08:42.245
This is old, this is new.
I'd like this instead of this.

01:08:42.384 --> 01:08:43.442
- Yes?
- Okay.

01:08:52.594 --> 01:08:54.562
WALLY:
Clearly, the assets in that fund were not...

01:08:54.697 --> 01:08:55.755
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

01:08:55.898 --> 01:08:57.058
Hang on.

01:08:57.199 --> 01:08:59.633
I gotta take this. Sorry, hold on.

01:09:00.269 --> 01:09:01.600
- Hello?
KASSIE [ON PHONE]: Wally?

01:09:01.737 --> 01:09:03.898
WALLY: Hi.
- Oh, thank God you picked up. Okay.

01:09:04.039 --> 01:09:08.942
- I'm in Michigan, and, um...
- Oh, at, uh, Camp Roland, huh?

01:09:09.078 --> 01:09:12.741
Uh, yes, Wally, I'm with Roland.
He's got a cabin up here.

01:09:12.881 --> 01:09:14.678
WALLY:
Been in the family for 30 years.

01:09:14.817 --> 01:09:17.615
Yeah, yeah, it has been.
How do you know that?

01:09:17.753 --> 01:09:21.211
- He told me.
