01:11:40.863 --> 01:11:43.525
you can strip both beds of pillowcases,
comforters and sheets.

01:11:43.665 --> 01:11:46.862
All right, we just gotta get
these few little things in here, please.

01:11:47.002 --> 01:11:50.995
And let me get this.
And I'll see you in a minute, okay?

01:11:51.139 --> 01:11:53.903
KASSIE: And then bag up all of
the throw pillows and stuffed animals.

01:11:54.042 --> 01:11:58.945
Make sure those bags are shut airtight
so those lice will suffocate.

01:11:59.081 --> 01:12:01.777
And throw everything in the wash
at the hottest temperature.

01:12:01.917 --> 01:12:03.384
WALLY:
Pass me the detergent, please.

01:12:03.519 --> 01:12:06.079
WALLY [ON PHONE]: This is not
enough steps. Can we add some more?

01:12:06.221 --> 01:12:08.348
Please just let me shave his head
and be done with it.

01:12:08.490 --> 01:12:10.287
KASSIE: Wally.
WALLY: Okay, okay.

01:12:10.425 --> 01:12:15.089
KASSIE: But whatever you do, Wally,
try not to make a big deal out of it.

01:12:15.564 --> 01:12:18.328
And make sure to follow the instructions
and wash his hair.

01:12:22.271 --> 01:12:25.798
Everything okay? You all right?
Are you doing okay?

01:12:27.743 --> 01:12:31.304
KASSIE: Oh, and just one more thing,
and it's sort of the worst part.

01:12:33.482 --> 01:12:35.746
There's this little comb.

01:12:35.884 --> 01:12:39.285
WALLY:
Oh, my God, this cannot be happening.

01:12:39.922 --> 01:12:40.980
- What?
- No, no, no.

01:12:41.123 --> 01:12:45.082
Just keep looking that way, pal.
Nothing's going on. Everything's good.

01:12:46.395 --> 01:12:48.056
[WALLY GROANS]

01:12:48.964 --> 01:12:52.661
Are they everywhere?
Are they climbing all over my head?

01:12:52.801 --> 01:12:54.166
Huh? No, they're fine.

01:12:54.303 --> 01:12:57.602
They're absolute... You're fine.
Everything's okay.

01:12:57.739 --> 01:12:58.865
Are you gonna throw up?

01:12:59.007 --> 01:13:01.703
No, I'm not gonna throw up.
I'm busy killing lice.

01:13:02.311 --> 01:13:06.111
SEBASTIAN: Did you find some?
- I think so.

01:13:06.682 --> 01:13:08.411
I got them.

01:13:13.589 --> 01:13:16.683
WALLY:
All right, hot out of the dryer.

01:13:16.825 --> 01:13:20.693
I think we are now officially deliced.

01:13:20.829 --> 01:13:23.662
Or "-loused," right? "Deloused"?

01:13:23.799 --> 01:13:26.529
Whatever it is,
we're down to DEFCON 1.

01:13:26.902 --> 01:13:30.804
Or is it 5?
Can never figure out which way that goes.

01:13:30.939 --> 01:13:32.497
All right, good night.

01:13:35.010 --> 01:13:37.501
Sweet dreams, okay?

01:13:39.114 --> 01:13:41.139
This is your collection, right? Huh?

01:13:45.287 --> 01:13:48.188
Why don't you wanna use any
of these frames?

01:13:48.857 --> 01:13:51.553
Why does everyone ask me that?

01:13:53.195 --> 01:13:56.130
Because, you know,
people like to put their own pictures

01:13:56.264 --> 01:13:58.095
inside their frames.

01:13:59.635 --> 01:14:01.830
But they already have pictures in them.

01:14:01.970 --> 01:14:03.995
That's true,
but you don't know any of these people.

01:14:04.139 --> 01:14:05.572
SEBASTIAN:
Sure I do.

01:14:06.074 --> 01:14:11.068
See, like these people.
This is the Owen family.

01:14:11.213 --> 01:14:15.513
That's Mr. And Mrs. Owen,
and those are their two kids.

01:14:16.451 --> 01:14:18.783
He studies volcanoes,

01:14:18.920 --> 01:14:25.849
and Mrs. Owen used to work for a place
that sells heart medicines for pets.

01:14:26.561 --> 01:14:28.119
WALLY:
Mm-hm.

01:14:28.563 --> 01:14:30.690
Well, that's funny,
because Mr. And Mrs. Owen

01:14:30.832 --> 01:14:33.232
look like third-rate
stock-photography models to me.

01:14:35.003 --> 01:14:36.527
That's my grandfather.

01:14:40.008 --> 01:14:41.908
- Which one, right here?
- Yeah.

01:14:42.044 --> 01:14:43.773
This guy?

01:14:45.180 --> 01:14:47.148
He's my father's dad.

01:14:47.916 --> 01:14:49.577
He owns a boat.

01:14:49.718 --> 01:14:53.711
He takes it out every day
to go fishing for sharks.

01:14:54.356 --> 01:14:56.517
And he knows a lot.

01:14:56.892 --> 01:14:58.519
[YAWNS]

01:14:58.860 --> 01:15:02.091
Did you know
that sharks don't have bones?

01:15:02.230 --> 01:15:04.664
No, but I do now.

01:15:06.601 --> 01:15:08.296
That's my Uncle Rick.

01:15:08.970 --> 01:15:11.302
He's my father's younger brother.

01:15:11.440 --> 01:15:14.170
- This guy here?
- Yeah.

01:15:16.144 --> 01:15:19.272
He got me an iPod for my birthday.

01:15:19.781 --> 01:15:25.549
But I think he stole it from somebody
because it already had music on it.

01:15:29.624 --> 01:15:31.854
What's your dad's family like?

01:15:32.761 --> 01:15:35.662
I don't know. I never met them.

01:15:36.431 --> 01:15:37.762
Why not?

01:15:38.934 --> 01:15:41.232
My father left when I was...

01:15:41.403 --> 01:15:43.803
When I was pretty young.

01:16:12.868 --> 01:16:15.063
You can keep it.

01:16:27.816 --> 01:16:29.647
WALLY:
Sweet dreams.

01:16:33.855 --> 01:16:35.220
[DOOR CLOSES]

01:16:38.426 --> 01:16:40.621
See, now, I think you put
too much flour in that, right?

01:16:40.762 --> 01:16:43.663
What you've got there is like a...
It's more like a paste, right?

01:16:43.799 --> 01:16:45.664
I mean, we could spackle these walls
with that.

01:16:45.801 --> 01:16:48.065
I think you need to put
a little bit more water in that.

01:16:48.203 --> 01:16:49.261
- All right?
- Okay.

01:16:49.404 --> 01:16:51.269
Let's think of something else
for the pancakes.

01:16:51.406 --> 01:16:52.464
[DOOR OPENS THEN CLOSES]

01:16:52.607 --> 01:16:53.904
What about, um, chocolate chips?

01:16:54.042 --> 01:16:56.806
Your mom got any of those?
Or what about peanut butter?

01:16:56.945 --> 01:16:58.310
SEBASTIAN: Maybe.
WALLY: Or cheese.

01:16:58.446 --> 01:17:00.141
Let's go the other way with it, right?

01:17:00.282 --> 01:17:02.580
Let's make it a little bit more
of a lunch pancake, right?

01:17:02.717 --> 01:17:06.084
- Why not? You like cheese?
- Let's put lice in the batter.

01:17:06.521 --> 01:17:10.116
What is so funny to you
about the concept of eating your lice?

01:17:10.258 --> 01:17:13.056
- I don't know, it's just funny.
- Are you looking for texture?

01:17:13.195 --> 01:17:16.164
If we burn them, you get a little crunch.
Keep your lice out of it.

01:17:16.298 --> 01:17:18.198
- Hi, hey.
KASSIE: Hello.

01:17:18.333 --> 01:17:22.030
- Mommy, I wanna show you the dead lice.
KASSIE: Come here, let me see that.

01:17:22.437 --> 01:17:23.870
- Come here.
SEBASTIAN: You're home.

01:17:24.005 --> 01:17:25.768
What do you have in that jar? Lice?

01:17:25.907 --> 01:17:27.101
- Lice.
- Are you kidding me?

01:17:27.242 --> 01:17:31.144
- Wally hunted them and killed them all.
- Let me see. I'm so sorry I wasn't here.

01:17:31.279 --> 01:17:33.611
- Is it all out?
- Yeah.

01:17:34.115 --> 01:17:35.173
- Oh, I love you.
- Me too.

01:17:35.317 --> 01:17:37.842
I'm gonna take the dead lice
to watch TV.

01:17:37.986 --> 01:17:39.146
That's a cute look.

01:17:39.988 --> 01:17:42.047
Oh, this is, um...

01:17:42.624 --> 01:17:45.320
I was starting to feel itchy,
so I used a little bit of the shampoo.

01:17:45.727 --> 01:17:47.319
You don't have lice.

01:17:48.063 --> 01:17:51.999
- Uh, I could. I could actually have lice.
- You don't have lice.

01:17:52.133 --> 01:17:55.899
And I really thank you.
I appreciate you taking care of all this.

01:17:56.037 --> 01:17:58.437
- Thanks for taking care of him.
- Yeah, you're welcome.

01:17:58.573 --> 01:18:01.133
- How was that weekend?
- It was good.

01:18:01.276 --> 01:18:05.406
It was good. It was really beautiful.
It's quiet, it's on the lake and...

01:18:05.547 --> 01:18:07.981
You know,
his grandfather actually built the cabin

01:18:08.116 --> 01:18:10.209
from logs that they milled
on the property, and so...

01:18:10.352 --> 01:18:11.979
[SNORES]

01:18:13.255 --> 01:18:17.316
And we're gonna go, I think,
in like two weeks, take Sebastian.

01:18:19.227 --> 01:18:20.922
Really? That's...

01:18:21.062 --> 01:18:23.155
- It's getting serious, huh?
- Yeah.

01:18:24.432 --> 01:18:29.096
We're actually, um,
thinking about moving in together.

01:18:31.840 --> 01:18:33.831
That's...

01:18:33.975 --> 01:18:36.603
I mean, you know, Kassie, I...

01:18:36.745 --> 01:18:39.179
- That's a mistake. I think that this guy...
- No, don't.

01:18:39.314 --> 01:18:40.781
- Is a mistake.

01:18:40.916 --> 01:18:42.816
Don't do this. Don't ruin this for me.

01:18:42.951 --> 01:18:44.145
- Hang on.
- No.

01:18:44.286 --> 01:18:45.810
Kassie.

01:18:46.354 --> 01:18:49.221
Come on, look, he started the year
married to someone else.

01:18:49.357 --> 01:18:51.757
Look, he's obviously going
through some kind of crap,

01:18:51.893 --> 01:18:53.190
and maybe he doesn't realize it,

01:18:53.328 --> 01:18:56.456
but it looks like he might be using you
and Sebastian to cushion the blow.

01:18:56.598 --> 01:19:01.058
You know that I actually thought
for a brief second that you changed?

01:19:01.202 --> 01:19:02.430
But you haven't.

01:19:02.570 --> 01:19:06.336
I'm trying to move forward with my life,
and you are exactly the same.

01:19:06.474 --> 01:19:08.874
The truth is, I'm actually happy.

01:19:09.010 --> 01:19:11.808
- Are you?
- Yes.

01:19:12.514 --> 01:19:17.315
Roland is a really good guy, all right?
He's supp... You know what?

01:19:17.452 --> 01:19:19.750
Just because you've never taken a risk
in your entire life

01:19:19.888 --> 01:19:21.549
doesn't mean
you have to rip apart mine.

01:19:22.657 --> 01:19:25.683
At least I'm trying to let somebody in.

01:19:25.827 --> 01:19:27.852
You should try it sometime.

01:19:27.996 --> 01:19:33.298
I mean, unless you have something else
that you would like to say to me.

01:19:34.903 --> 01:19:36.165
Wally?

01:19:38.006 --> 01:19:39.940
Really? Got nothing for me, huh?

01:19:40.075 --> 01:19:41.337
[DOOR OPENS]

01:19:41.476 --> 01:19:45.344
- Nothing?
ROLAND: Ooh. Do I smell flapjacks?

01:19:45.480 --> 01:19:49.348
Hey, Wally,
thanks for being on lice patrol, man.

01:19:49.484 --> 01:19:52.351
You gotta try some of this beer
Grandma made.

01:19:56.124 --> 01:19:58.456
[EELS' "ALL THE BEAUTIFUL
THINGS"PLAYING]

01:21:01.523 --> 01:21:02.990
[DOORBELL RINGS]

01:21:04.159 --> 01:21:05.626
[PANTING]

01:21:06.928 --> 01:21:08.828
Sebastian, what's going on?
What happened?

01:21:08.963 --> 01:21:12.490
I was at Ethan's birthday party
and I did what you told me to.

01:21:13.001 --> 01:21:15.265
Aaron O'Connor was there.

01:21:15.403 --> 01:21:17.928
I stood up to him and acted crazy.

01:21:23.144 --> 01:21:25.078
Look at your face.

01:21:25.213 --> 01:21:27.681
He punched me
and then threw me into a puddle

01:21:27.816 --> 01:21:29.545
and then hit me again.

01:21:29.684 --> 01:21:31.242
Come here.

01:21:32.220 --> 01:21:35.712
- He didn't care that I was crazy.
- Shh. It's okay.

01:21:35.857 --> 01:21:38.826
It didn't work, I tried.

01:21:39.427 --> 01:21:41.520
Where was this? Where was the party?

01:21:41.663 --> 01:21:44.632
- At the park.
- Which park?

01:21:44.766 --> 01:21:48.702
- East End.
- East End Park?

01:21:48.837 --> 01:21:51.362
That's like 20 blocks away from here.

01:21:52.373 --> 01:21:54.341
Um, I'm gonna call your mom
to come get you.

01:21:54.476 --> 01:21:57.309
No, Wally, you have to take me home.

01:22:00.482 --> 01:22:02.916
Take me home, Wally.

01:22:04.652 --> 01:22:07.177
Sebastian, why did you come here?

01:22:08.623 --> 01:22:11.820
Because I thought you'd be proud of me.

01:22:14.662 --> 01:22:15.463
[DOOR BUZZES]

01:22:15.463 --> 01:22:16.487
[DOOR BUZZES]

01:22:19.634 --> 01:22:22.728
Oh, my God, honey,
what happened to you?

01:22:22.871 --> 01:22:26.068
- I got into a fight.
KASSIE: Sweetie, oh, my God.

01:22:26.207 --> 01:22:28.402
- Why didn't Donna call me?
- It's actually my fault.

01:22:28.543 --> 01:22:32.206
I told him to do something really stupid
a while back, and he listened to me.

01:22:32.347 --> 01:22:35.282
But he's fine.
He came over to my place and...

01:22:35.416 --> 01:22:37.611
KASSIE:
He came to you?

01:22:38.319 --> 01:22:40.446
- Yeah, and...
ROLAND: I thought I heard the doorbell.

01:22:40.588 --> 01:22:43.921
WALLY: Oh, what's going on?
- Oh, Roland's family is in town.

01:22:44.058 --> 01:22:45.423
We're just having a little brunch.

01:22:45.560 --> 01:22:47.289
- Hey, Wally.
- Who beat the kid?

01:22:48.329 --> 01:22:50.661
KASSIE: Come on, let's go.
DEBBIE: Sweetie, come here.

01:22:50.798 --> 01:22:52.766
Oh, my God, you're covered in dirt.

01:22:52.901 --> 01:22:54.994
KASSIE: Come on, honey,
let's go get cleaned up.

01:22:55.136 --> 01:22:57.127
DEBBIE:
We'll fix you up.

01:22:58.873 --> 01:23:00.738
Let's go in the kitchen.

01:23:00.875 --> 01:23:03.070
Somebody punched you?

01:23:03.211 --> 01:23:04.701
- Hey, Wally.
- Yeah?

01:23:04.846 --> 01:23:05.904
What happened?

01:23:06.047 --> 01:23:08.311
- He got in a fight with another kid.
- Oh, that's awful.

01:23:08.449 --> 01:23:10.679
- Yeah.
- You know, but it'll make him stronger.

01:23:10.818 --> 01:23:14.845
I took a few lumps when I was a kid,
usually at the hands of my older brothers.

01:23:14.989 --> 01:23:16.980
- Who are here. You gotta meet them.
- Okay.

01:23:17.125 --> 01:23:19.184
Oh, wait, hold on.

01:23:21.696 --> 01:23:23.425
Check it out.

01:23:24.065 --> 01:23:25.532
Right?

01:23:28.036 --> 01:23:30.834
Stick around. It's gonna get good.

01:23:34.375 --> 01:23:36.240
I'm sorry, Roland.

01:23:37.078 --> 01:23:38.705
[SCOFFS]

01:23:39.547 --> 01:23:41.310
For what?

01:23:41.449 --> 01:23:43.349
KASSIE: Doesn't feel that bad, huh?
- No.

01:23:43.484 --> 01:23:44.712
WALLY: Hey.
KASSIE: Not really?

01:23:44.852 --> 01:23:47.116
SEBASTIAN: I'm okay.
- I really do need to talk to you.

01:23:47.722 --> 01:23:48.916
Act crazy, Wally?

01:23:49.057 --> 01:23:51.855
Remind me to never to ask you for advice
when I'm being bullied.

01:23:51.993 --> 01:23:54.928
What do you want from me, Debbie?
I'm an idiot. Kassie, this cannot wait.

01:23:55.997 --> 01:23:57.521
- Debbie...?
- I got it, and I'm sorry.

01:23:57.665 --> 01:23:58.723
I will be right back.

01:23:58.866 --> 01:24:01.426
- It was just talk.
- Thanks.

01:24:05.373 --> 01:24:07.637
What got into him?

01:24:08.343 --> 01:24:10.504
You wanna try these peas?

01:24:10.912 --> 01:24:13.278
All right, Wally, what is it?

01:24:13.414 --> 01:24:14.938
I, uh...

01:24:15.083 --> 01:24:18.484
There she is.
Hey, Kass, Wally, come on in.

01:24:18.620 --> 01:24:20.611
Yeah, come on in, take a seat.

01:24:20.755 --> 01:24:22.313
- Listen, hang on one second.
- I can't.

01:24:22.457 --> 01:24:25.824
Kass, come on in. You too, Wally.

01:24:25.960 --> 01:24:28.155
KASSIE: Okay.
- Come on, take a seat.

01:24:28.296 --> 01:24:29.456
Everybody listen up.

01:24:29.964 --> 01:24:31.022
Hush, hush.

01:24:31.165 --> 01:24:32.359
[ROLAND CHUCKLES]

01:24:33.067 --> 01:24:34.694
Got a little something to say. Everybody.

01:24:34.836 --> 01:24:36.167
[GLASS CLINKING]

01:24:36.304 --> 01:24:37.362
All right.

01:24:37.505 --> 01:24:38.904
[ROLAND CLEARS THROAT]

01:24:39.040 --> 01:24:41.099
A few months ago,

01:24:41.609 --> 01:24:45.170
and I'm not gonna lie,
I was, uh, in a dark place.

01:24:46.047 --> 01:24:48.982
- Um, I was in a world of pain.
WALLY [WHISPERING]: Kassie. Kassie.

01:24:49.117 --> 01:24:50.744
I really have to talk to you.

01:24:50.885 --> 01:24:52.614
ROLAND: My wife, ex-wife...
- Stop.

01:24:52.754 --> 01:24:57.555
- Had left me for reasons
that I don't need to get into now.

01:24:57.692 --> 01:24:59.819
WALLY:
Over here, right now.

01:24:59.961 --> 01:25:02.225
- And then...
- It's gotta be now. Trust me this is real.

01:25:02.363 --> 01:25:03.830
...one day...
- Cut it out.

01:25:03.965 --> 01:25:05.057
- The heavens opened,

01:25:06.367 --> 01:25:11.236
and the sweet voice of an angel
is on my phone machine.

01:25:11.372 --> 01:25:12.669
[KASSIE CHUCKLES]

01:25:13.074 --> 01:25:17.408
And I am happy to say
to you all that I love,

01:25:17.879 --> 01:25:21.212
that my life is whole again.

01:25:21.349 --> 01:25:23.579
Today Sebastian
scared the hell out of me.

01:25:23.718 --> 01:25:25.879
Wally, take a seat,
I'm about to get to the good stuff.

01:25:26.020 --> 01:25:28.818
Roland, I'm sorry, you're a really good guy.
I hate to do this to you.

01:25:28.956 --> 01:25:31.049
ROLAND: Hate to do what?
- Throw this curveball.

01:25:31.793 --> 01:25:35.854
When Sebastian needed someone today,
Kassie, he came to me.

01:25:35.997 --> 01:25:40.400
You know, he needed me.
And I need him.

01:25:40.968 --> 01:25:42.731
All right,
what are you talking about, Wally?

01:25:42.870 --> 01:25:45.668
I'm talking about something
I haven't been able to say before, Kassie.

01:25:45.807 --> 01:25:47.399
I, uh...

01:25:47.709 --> 01:25:48.767
[SIGHS]

01:25:48.910 --> 01:25:54.507
I hijacked your pregnancy.

01:25:55.583 --> 01:25:57.642
I'm the seed guy.

01:26:03.958 --> 01:26:05.289
What?

01:26:05.426 --> 01:26:11.990
I replaced, uh, Roland's offering
with mine that night,

01:26:12.133 --> 01:26:13.327
your party.

01:26:13.468 --> 01:26:15.095
Um...

01:26:15.236 --> 01:26:16.464
[MURMURING]

01:26:17.538 --> 01:26:20.166
Sebastian's my son.

01:26:21.008 --> 01:26:26.071
I know it was a reckless and careless
and terrible thing to do,

01:26:26.214 --> 01:26:27.704
but, I mean, I panicked, you know.

01:26:27.849 --> 01:26:30.374
I'm not like you, you know.

01:26:30.518 --> 01:26:33.544
You're not afraid of anything.
I'm afraid of everything.

01:26:33.688 --> 01:26:35.553
I can't even take risks, you know,
you said it.

01:26:35.690 --> 01:26:38.250
But nothing scares you, Kassie,
and I love that about you.

01:26:39.861 --> 01:26:42.659
I mean, you're gonna hate me
the rest of your life,

01:26:42.797 --> 01:26:45.630
and you're never gonna forgive me,
and I don't expect you to forgive me.

01:26:45.767 --> 01:26:49.294
It just... It breaks my heart, it kills me,

01:26:49.437 --> 01:26:52.873
because he's changed me.

01:26:53.207 --> 01:26:56.608
You've changed me, and, um...

01:26:59.914 --> 01:27:01.506
...I love you.

01:27:09.590 --> 01:27:13.048
I couldn't say that before,
but I'm saying it right now.

01:27:18.699 --> 01:27:21.361
And I'm also saying I'm sorry.

01:27:21.502 --> 01:27:23.800
I'm really sorry.

01:27:30.445 --> 01:27:32.379
DEBBIE:
Good we got that dirt off.

01:27:36.317 --> 01:27:38.251
Don't ever speak to us again.

01:27:45.927 --> 01:27:47.326
What did I miss?

01:27:47.462 --> 01:27:48.895
[DOOR CLOSES]

01:27:55.603 --> 01:27:58.299
WALLY:
Sorry about your proposal, Roland.

01:27:58.439 --> 01:28:00.373
His what?

01:28:01.909 --> 01:28:03.934
Oh, my God.

01:28:15.056 --> 01:28:17.149
I am proud of you.

01:28:33.574 --> 01:28:34.632
[DOORBELL RINGING]

01:28:57.198 --> 01:29:01.396
- Wally, it's 4 a.m.
WALLY: I did it.

01:29:01.536 --> 01:29:03.595
I did the right thing, Leonard.

01:29:04.071 --> 01:29:07.199
- Come on in.
- I faced my fear, I told her.

01:29:07.341 --> 01:29:10.902
That's good, Wally. That's real good.

01:29:11.045 --> 01:29:14.879
But I lost her. And Sebastian.

01:29:16.784 --> 01:29:19.150
You did the right thing.
I'm proud of you, Wally.

01:29:19.921 --> 01:29:22.583
- It sucks.
- But it'll get better.

01:29:22.723 --> 01:29:27.126
You know,
I'm drinking booze from a deli.

01:29:30.064 --> 01:29:32.259
You should go home, Wally.

01:29:34.902 --> 01:29:37.166
They are my home, Leonard.

01:29:37.305 --> 01:29:40.001
[EELS' "NUMBERED DAYS"PLAYING]

01:30:58.019 --> 01:30:59.884
[HORNS HONKING]

01:31:21.609 --> 01:31:26.069
So I've thought about it, and, uh,

01:31:26.213 --> 01:31:30.411
you can't just disappear
from Sebastian's life.

01:31:30.551 --> 01:31:32.314
So...

01:31:32.453 --> 01:31:33.715
You know, he's your son.

01:31:36.123 --> 01:31:39.786
And of course you can see him.

01:31:39.927 --> 01:31:42.122
But it's gonna be on my terms.

01:31:46.333 --> 01:31:48.096
How's he doing?

01:31:49.470 --> 01:31:50.630
He misses you.

01:31:51.238 --> 01:31:54.469
- I miss him.
- A lot.

01:31:54.608 --> 01:31:57.805
Is he...?
How's he getting along with Roland, okay?

01:31:58.512 --> 01:32:00.104
Yeah.

01:32:01.415 --> 01:32:02.882
I, uh...

01:32:03.751 --> 01:32:05.946
I couldn't go through with that.

01:32:09.056 --> 01:32:11.490
- What happened? What do you mean?
- I don't know.

01:32:12.393 --> 01:32:14.156
[CHUCKLES]

01:32:14.562 --> 01:32:16.621
He's affectionate.

01:32:17.331 --> 01:32:19.299
Likes me to try new things.

01:32:20.134 --> 01:32:22.728
He doesn't turn into a psycho
when he drinks.

01:32:22.870 --> 01:32:26.169
He doesn't moan when he eats.

01:32:29.110 --> 01:32:31.874
I turned him down because he's not you.

01:32:49.163 --> 01:32:50.391
Will you marry me?

01:32:52.566 --> 01:32:54.534
Probably.

01:33:17.525 --> 01:33:19.288
WALLY:
Look at us.

01:33:20.594 --> 01:33:22.255
Running around,

01:33:22.396 --> 01:33:26.423
always rushed, always late.

01:33:27.201 --> 01:33:29.931
Guess that's why they call it
the human race.

01:33:32.106 --> 01:33:38.067
But sometimes it slows down just enough
for all the pieces to fall into place.

01:33:40.481 --> 01:33:43.075
Fate works its magic.

01:33:45.519 --> 01:33:47.453
And you're connected.

01:33:48.956 --> 01:33:51.356
KASSIE: Oh. Hi.
WALLY: You smell that?

01:33:51.492 --> 01:33:53.858
- What is that?
- That's charcoal, lighter fluid,

01:33:53.994 --> 01:33:55.222
and my burnt arm hairs.

01:33:55.362 --> 01:33:57.023
- Is that working for you at all?
- Oh.

01:33:58.732 --> 01:34:00.757
Shame there are all these children
around.

01:34:00.901 --> 01:34:01.959
I don't mind an audience.

01:34:02.102 --> 01:34:03.626
- You don't?
- No, they'll seem like my team.

01:34:03.771 --> 01:34:07.673
Oh, God, no. Honey, here, ice cream.
Take this out there, but be careful.

01:34:07.808 --> 01:34:10.868
One of these children has a milk allergy,
and I have no clue which one it is.

01:34:11.011 --> 01:34:12.569
It might be the little blond one there.

01:34:12.713 --> 01:34:14.408
- Just go with a sorbet or something?
- No.

01:34:14.548 --> 01:34:16.243
- You sure?
- No, no.

01:34:24.058 --> 01:34:28.791
[ALL SINGING
"HAPPY BIRTHDAY TO YOU"]

01:34:47.815 --> 01:34:49.282
KID: Yeah, Sebastian!
KASSIE: Whoo!

01:34:49.416 --> 01:34:51.611
KIDS:
Yeah, Sebastian!

01:34:52.286 --> 01:34:54.015
LEONARD:
Yeah, yeah.

01:34:54.154 --> 01:34:56.281
WALLY: Nice.
- How about that?

01:34:56.423 --> 01:35:01.622
Now, this year, Sebastian has decided
to dedicate his birthday to Doug.

01:35:01.762 --> 01:35:02.820
And Doug is a...

01:35:02.963 --> 01:35:07.900
He's just a wonderful, uh, playful,
three-legged dog,

01:35:08.035 --> 01:35:11.869
and, um, he's in need of a home, so...

01:35:12.773 --> 01:35:13.933
And?

01:35:15.542 --> 01:35:19.000
And, um, well, Doug is, uh...

01:35:19.146 --> 01:35:22.673
He's next in line at the kill shelter
to be put down.

01:35:22.816 --> 01:35:25.341
Oh, that would be a horrible way to go.

01:35:25.753 --> 01:35:28.813
- But not dead yet. Very much alive.
- That's so good. Positive thinking.

01:35:28.956 --> 01:35:30.218
- Happy puppy.
- And, yeah.

01:35:30.357 --> 01:35:33.326
Let's go ahead and blow out the candles.
Get some of that cake in our face.

01:35:33.460 --> 01:35:37.021
I'm not blowing out anything
until someone takes Doug.

01:35:38.332 --> 01:35:40.095
WOMAN:
Okay.

01:35:40.234 --> 01:35:41.929
Well, I'll take him.

01:35:42.069 --> 01:35:43.661
- Debbie Epstein.
- Thank you.

01:35:43.804 --> 01:35:44.862
Debbie Epstein.

01:35:45.339 --> 01:35:48.536
I can handle him.
He's only got three legs. That's...

01:35:48.676 --> 01:35:50.200
MAN:
All right.

01:35:50.744 --> 01:35:54.805
- Surprising.
- Okay, make a wish, baby. Come on.

01:35:55.482 --> 01:35:56.881
WALLY: Harder.
KASSIE: There you go.

01:35:57.017 --> 01:35:58.245
Really well done. One more.

01:35:58.385 --> 01:35:59.784
LEONARD: Here I come.
KASSIE: Yes.

01:35:59.920 --> 01:36:00.978
[ALL CHEERING]

01:36:01.121 --> 01:36:03.316
KID 1: Happy birthday.
KID 2: Happy birthday, Sebastian.

01:36:03.457 --> 01:36:05.220
KASSIE:
I love you, baby, sweet cheeks.

01:36:05.359 --> 01:36:08.886
WALLY: Every once in a while,
amid all the randomness,

01:36:09.463 --> 01:36:13.957
something unexpected happens,
and it pushes us all forward.

01:36:14.301 --> 01:36:18.795
And the truth is,
what I'm starting to think,

01:36:18.939 --> 01:36:21.567
what I'm starting to feel,

01:36:23.777 --> 01:36:27.372
is that maybe the human race

01:36:28.582 --> 01:36:31.415
isn't a race at all.

01:36:37.491 --> 01:36:40.016
[BIBIO'S "LO VERS' CARVINGS"
PLAYING]